All documentation must be maintained. Whether it is runa syntax, runa grammar, instructions for use and development, and anything else that may be supportive of the development, maintenance, and prolonged use of Runa. This means, there should always be documentation updates during development, which will include docs that say what was done and what needs to be done, docs that will detail what can be done and how to write/work in runa, and docs that detail the grammar and syntax for new users in the future.